About Me

Exploring the intersection of mathematics, finance, and artificial intelligence

Background

I'm a Masters student in Computational Mathematical Engineering at Stanford University, with a specialization in Mathematical Computational Finance. My work focuses on applying advanced mathematical methods and machine learning to solve complex problems in quantitative finance.

My research interests lie at the intersection of AI, mathematics, and finance, where I explore innovative approaches to risk modeling, algorithmic trading, and financial optimization.
